abstract: U.S. President Donald Trump arrived on Monday in the western Indian city of Ahmedabad for a two-day trip aimed at reinvigorating ties between the world's biggest democracies that have been strained by trade rows.
snippet: U.S. President Donald Trump arrived on Monday in the western Indian city of Ahmedabad for a two-day trip aimed at reinvigorating ties between the world's biggest democracies that have been strained by trade rows.
lead_paragraph: AHMEDABAD, India — U.S. President Donald Trump arrived on Monday in the western Indian city of Ahmedabad for a two-day trip aimed at reinvigorating ties between the world's biggest democracies that have been strained by trade rows.
headline_main: Trump Lands in Western Indian City for Start of Two-Day Visit
headline_print_headline: Trump Lands in Western Indian City for Start of Two-Day Visit

abstract: Prioritizing pageantry over policy, President Donald Trump basked in India's welcoming embrace on a day that featured a mega-rally with cheering crowds, a mutual admiration show with his counterpart and a sunset tour of the famed Taj Mahal.

abstract: With Israel's prime minister eager to court the votes of the country's influential West Bank settlers, President Donald Trump's Mideast plan seemed to be the key to ramping up their support ahead of critical elections next week.

lead_paragraph: ATERET, West Bank — With Israel's prime minister eager to court the votes of the country's influential West Bank settlers, President Donald Trump's Mideast plan seemed to be the key to ramping up their support ahead of critical elections next week.
headline_main: Netanyahu Banks on Trump Plan to Drive Up Pro-Settler Votes

abstract: In their boisterous presidential debate, several Democrats sold short the health care plans of rivals and Mike Bloomberg distorted his position on the “stop and frisk" police strategy when he was New York City mayor. In an audacious league of his own, President Donald Trump celebrated the elimination of a tax that still exists and went deep and wide in distorting what he's done in office.

lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — In their boisterous presidential debate, several Democrats sold short the health care plans of rivals and Mike Bloomberg distorted his position on the “stop and frisk" police strategy when he was New York City mayor. In an audacious league of his own, President Donald Trump celebrated the elimination of a tax that still exists and went deep and wide in distorting what he's done in office.
headline_main: AP FACT CHECK: Trump's Tax Fictions; Dem Debate Misfires
headline_print_headline: AP FACT CHECK: Trump's Tax Fictions; Dem Debate Misfires

abstract: A man held up a hostile poster a few rows behind Michigan Rep. Elissa Slotkin as she spoke. On other side of the room, allies hoisted a Slotkin-friendly banner. But what was perhaps most striking at Slotkin's first town hall since President Donald Trump's impeachment was a newfound sense of civility.
snippet: A man held up a hostile poster a few rows behind Michigan Rep. Elissa Slotkin as she spoke. On other side of the room, allies hoisted a Slotkin-friendly banner. But what was perhaps most striking at Slotkin's first town hall since President Donald...
lead_paragraph: EAST LANSING, Mich. — A man held up a hostile poster a few rows behind Michigan Rep. Elissa Slotkin as she spoke. On other side of the room, allies hoisted a Slotkin-friendly banner. But what was perhaps most striking at Slotkin's first town hall since President Donald Trump's impeachment was a newfound sense of civility.
headline_main: Impeachment Fades for Slotkin as Democrats Try to Pivot Away
headline_print_headline: Impeachment Fades for Slotkin as Democrats Try to Pivot Away

lead_paragraph: Italy locked down the Lombardy region, halting life for around 50,000 people in 10 towns, after more than 150 coronavirus cases appeared in the country in just a few days. Three people have died and 26 were in intensive care, asEurope began confronting one of the most serious tests yet of open borders.

abstract: Donald Trump was cheered by more than 100,000 Indians at the opening of the world's largest cricket stadium on Monday, promising "an incredible trade deal" and "the most feared military equipment on the planet" at his biggest rally abroad.
snippet: Donald Trump was cheered by more than 100,000 Indians at the opening of the world's largest cricket stadium on Monday, promising "an incredible trade deal" and "the most feared military equipment on the planet" at his biggest rally abroad.
lead_paragraph: AHMEDABAD, India — Donald Trump was cheered by more than 100,000 Indians at the opening of the world's largest cricket stadium on Monday, promising "an incredible trade deal" and "the most feared military equipment on the planet" at his biggest rally abroad.
headline_main: 'Namaste Trump': Modi Holds Huge Rally for President's Visit
headline_print_headline: 'Namaste Trump': Modi Holds Huge Rally for President's Visit

abstract: Worried Democrats on Monday intensified their assault against the party's presidential front-runner, Bernie Sanders, as the Vermont senator marched toward South Carolina's weekend primary eyeing a knockout blow.
snippet: Worried Democrats on Monday intensified their assault against the party's presidential front-runner, Bernie Sanders, as the Vermont senator marched toward South Carolina's weekend primary eyeing a knockout blow.
lead_paragraph: HILTON HEAD ISLAND, S.C. — Worried Democrats on Monday intensified their assault against the party's presidential front-runner, Bernie Sanders, as the Vermont senator marched toward South Carolina's weekend primary eyeing a knockout blow.
headline_main: Worried Democrats Rush to Slow Front-Runner Sanders

abstract: Nearly two-thirds of U.S. business economists say the Federal Reserve's interest rate policy is “about right,” a sharp contrast to President Donald Trump's attacks on the Fed for not cutting rates more aggressively.
snippet: Nearly two-thirds of U.S. business economists say the Federal Reserve's interest rate policy is “about right,” a sharp contrast to President Donald Trump's attacks on the Fed for not cutting rates more aggressively.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Nearly two-thirds of U.S. business economists say the Federal Reserve's interest rate policy is “about right,” a sharp contrast to President Donald Trump's attacks on the Fed for not cutting rates more aggressively.
headline_main: Survey: Business Economists Endorse Federal Reserve Policies
headline_print_headline: Survey: Business Economists Endorse Federal Reserve Policies
